Setting up the envirotnment.

To install angular CLI in a project that you already have, you`ll use the following :
npm i @angular/cli

when you install it in a folder, it will install all the node_modules creating a folder and the package-lock.json file.

to start server, you will use
ng serve

to create a project
ng new project_name

to create a component, you will use 
ng g c component_name

to install bootstrap in your project, you will use the following :
npm install bootstrap --save

